               <p>
                  <rs id="t18270712-69-viclabel382" type="occupation">COLONEL</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270712-69-victim476 t18270712-69-viclabel382"></join> JOHN ROSS. I am <rs id="t18270712-69-viclabel383" type="occupation">in the Army</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270712-69-victim476 t18270712-69-viclabel383"></join>. I was in <placeName id="t18270712-69-crimeloc384">Regent-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18270712-69-crimeloc384" type="placeName" value="Regent-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18270712-69-crimeloc384" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270712-69-off379 t18270712-69-crimeloc384"></join> about eleven o'clock on Sunday evening, the 10th of June - I felt a motion at my coat pocket; I put my hand down, and missed my handkerchief; I turned, and caught hold of the prisoner close at my elbow, with it in his hand - I gave him in charge.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. J. ALLEY. Q. Were there not many persons passing? A. Yes. I am sure he was close to my back; I did not see him stoop - he made no resistance.</p>
               <p>JURY. Q. Was the prisoner nearest to you? A. Yes, so close that I immediately took hold of him; he begged to be allowed to go. I am convinced almost that it was his first offence, and I beg to recommend him to mercy.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270712-69-person477">
                  THOMAS 
                  GOOK
